  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My brother was, at the time, 19 years old.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He had rightly judged the coming persecution on hand of what he witnessed, as I described it, with the humiliations that he saw.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He then decided to escape into the eastern part of Poland, the part that was then occupied by the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we received letters, from my brother, that he is in contact with our family there, and that he has an opportunity, or may have an opportunity, to study medicine in Leningrad, which was his-- it-- it-- it was his dream to become a physician, since he was a youngster.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But my mother could not stop crying and could not stop worrying about him being with the Russians.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Some of this had to do with the traditional respect for religion.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it-- it was just unthinkable that a godless society can be more humane than-- than the Western educated and talented Germans.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so, she thought that he would be safer and better off if he returned to Gorlice, where our family was.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Eventually, he did return.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And of course, they were killed together, my mother and him, same day, same place.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that leads to another story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But-- but the moral of this story was that all too many of us believed that the Western Germans would still be more respectful of life than the ungodly Soviets, a fallacy that cost not only the life of my brother but of many who thought the same way.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] because I mentioned that my brother and my mother died together, they were taken away from Gorlice to Belzec.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
